{
  "stem": "12904.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And had to justify to our lawyers that we could use our relief fund because I felt that intellectual stimulation and socialization was as important to people in old age-- I recognized that in the early '70s when I was not a senior citizen, yet-- was as important as eating or drinking or sleeping.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And so we were allowed to use the money, the interest from a fund, a relief fund, for a taxi service.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, very much so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, I remember very much the D-Day and V-E Day and all those.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was still in the service.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was still at Fort Lewis at that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I, of course, knew a lot of soldiers-- we had the soldiers who came back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a lot of people coming back from the Pacific.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as much as I have been opposed to nuclear-- to the bomb, atomic bomb and nuclear war in general nuclear, I can't forget the pictures of the soldiers that I worked with who came back paralyzed, totally-- you know, extremely bad shape some of them.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some of them who told their fiances that they couldn't marry them and to just forget about them and things like that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was, I think, very, very difficult.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then I have felt-- I used to go to our celebration-- well, it was not a real celebration-- against the nuclear bombing, against the atomic bomb.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "On August 6th we would-- the Hiroshima bombing used to be celebrated here locally-- and I haven't gone anymore the last two or three years-- because I was thinking of the injured soldiers that I worked with, that I saw.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So, you know, the Japanese were not totally innocent as some would want you to believe.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
